docs.lead_paragraph: Officials are worried that companies with healthy employees will self-insure, leaving commercial insurers with disproportionate numbers of sicker people, driving up premiums.

headline.seo: Allure of Self-Insurance Draws Concern Over Costs
headline.main: Some Employers Could Opt Out of Insurance Market, Raising Others’ Costs
headline.print_headline: Employers With Healthy Workers Could Opt Out of Insurance Market, Raising Others’ Costs

docs.abstract: Federal and state officials, along with consumer advocates, worry that companies with relatively young, healthy employees will choose to opt out of the regular health insurance market; self-insurance allows employers to avoid minimum coverage standards under health reform laws.
docs.snippet: Officials are worried that companies with healthy employees will self-insure, leaving commercial insurers with disproportionate numbers of sicker people, driving up premiums.
